New Records: Algeria has a 16-game unbeaten streak in AFCON qualifiers since 2007, last losing an away match in 2018.
Togo has struggled defensively in their qualifying campaign, conceding three goals in their first two matches.
Pre-Game Insights: Algeria is confident due to their strong home record and recent winning streak under manager Vladimir Petkovic.
Togo needs a win to maintain their qualification hopes and will face challenges against Algeria's strong attack.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Togo's talisman Kodjo Laba is absent, while Algeria includes several new players in their squad.
